WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:00.603 --> 00:00:02.641
I'm giving you half
<i>of our forces.</i>

2
00:00:02.643 --> 00:00:05.317
You will bring them
to Catelyn Stark's girlhood home

3
00:00:05.351 --> 00:00:09.260
and remind her that
Lannisters pay their debts.

4
00:00:09.294 --> 00:00:11.500
- Do you love your children?
- With all my heart.

5
00:00:11.535 --> 00:00:14.205
- No more than I love mine.
- And they're all Jaime's.

6
00:00:14.239 --> 00:00:17.242
Jaime and I are more than brother
and sister. We belong together.

7
00:00:17.276 --> 00:00:20.210
When the King returns from his
hunt. I'll tell him the truth.

8
00:00:20.244 --> 00:00:21.911
You must
be gone by then.

9
00:00:23.280 --> 00:00:24.613
There's no rider.

10
00:00:24.647 --> 00:00:27.516
That's my Uncle Benjen's horse.
Where's my Uncle?

11
00:00:28.751 --> 00:00:30.485
- What's he got there?
- To me. Ghost.

12
00:00:30.519 --> 00:00:32.820
Gods be good!

13
00:00:32.855 --> 00:00:35.323
Ned!
It's Robert.

14
00:00:35.357 --> 00:00:36.893
<i>We were hunting a boar.</i>

15
00:00:36.928 --> 00:00:40.465
Give it to the Council
after I'm dead.

16
00:00:40.499 --> 00:00:43.372
He named you Protector of the Realm.
She won't care.

17
00:00:43.406 --> 00:00:45.409
Give me an hour and I can put
100 swords at your command.

18
00:00:45.443 --> 00:00:48.245
Every moment you delay gives
Cersei another moment to prepare.

19
00:00:48.280 --> 00:00:51.782
I will not dishonor Robert's last
hours by shedding blood in his halls.

20
00:00:51.816 --> 00:00:53.952
King Robert
still wants me dead.

21
00:00:53.986 --> 00:00:56.555
<i>This poisoner was the first.</i>
<i>he won't be the last.</i>

22
00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:04.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

23
00:01:09.107 --> 00:01:11.775
King Joffrey and the Queen Regent
request your presence in the throne room.

24
00:01:11.810 --> 00:01:14.311
- King Joffrey?
- King Robert is gone.

25
00:01:14.345 --> 00:01:17.613
Bend the knee and swear
loyalty to my son.

26
00:01:17.648 --> 00:01:19.615
Your son has no claim
to the throne.

27
00:01:19.649 --> 00:01:21.683
Kill him!
Kill all of them. I command it!

28
00:01:26.222 --> 00:01:29.524
I did warn you
not to trust me.

29
00:01:39.294 --> 00:01:43.294
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Game of Thrones 01x08 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>The Pointy End</font>
Original Air Date on June 5. 2011

30
00:01:43.319 --> 00:01:47.319
== sync. corrected by <font color="#00ff00">elderman</font> ==

31
00:03:26.425 --> 00:03:29.160
Yah!
Left high. left low.

32
00:03:46.746 --> 00:03:48.814
Right low.
lunge right.

33
00:03:51.984 --> 00:03:54.685
You break anything.
the Septa will have my head.

34
00:03:54.719 --> 00:03:56.520
What is--

35
00:04:07.597 --> 00:04:10.365
Your sister knew perfectly
well we were to leave today.

36
00:04:10.399 --> 00:04:12.567
- How she could forget--
- She didn't forget.

37
00:04:12.601 --> 00:04:15.303
She's with her dancing master.
She's with him every morning.

38
00:04:15.337 --> 00:04:17.873
She always comes back with scrapes
and bruises. She's so clumsy.

39
00:04:17.907 --> 00:04:19.808
Hush!

40
00:04:19.843 --> 00:04:22.044
Go back to your room.

41
00:04:22.979 --> 00:04:24.381
Bar the doors

42
00:04:24.415 --> 00:04:26.616
and do not open them for anyone
you do not know.

43
00:04:26.651 --> 00:04:29.319
- What is it? What's happening?
- Do as I told you.

44
00:04:29.354 --> 00:04:31.155
Run!

45
00:04:34.893 --> 00:04:36.560
<i>This way!</i>

46
00:04:50.072 --> 00:04:52.240
Left. right.
Rah!

47
00:04:52.274 --> 00:04:53.975
Now you are dead.

48
00:04:54.009 --> 00:04:55.977
You said right.

49
00:04:56.011 --> 00:04:57.879
but you went left.

50
00:04:57.913 --> 00:05:00.114
And now you are
a dead girl.

51
00:05:00.148 --> 00:05:01.749
Only 'cause you lied.

52
00:05:01.784 --> 00:05:04.418
My tongue lied.
My eyes

53
00:05:04.452 --> 00:05:07.655
shouted the truth.
You were not seeing.

54
00:05:07.689 --> 00:05:10.191
I was so.
I watched. but you--

55
00:05:10.225 --> 00:05:13.695
Watching is not seeing.
dead girl.

56
00:05:15.765 --> 00:05:19.401
The seeing.
the true seeing.

57
00:05:19.435 --> 00:05:21.871
that is the heart
of swordplay.

58
00:05:26.377 --> 00:05:28.879
Arya Stark.
come with us.

59
00:05:28.913 --> 00:05:31.649
Your father wants
to see you.

60
00:05:31.683 --> 00:05:34.051
And why is it

61
00:05:34.085 --> 00:05:36.520
that Lord Eddard is
sending Lannister men

62
00:05:36.554 --> 00:05:38.756
in place of his own?
I am wondering.

63
00:05:38.790 --> 00:05:41.859
Mind your place.
dancing master.

64
00:05:41.893 --> 00:05:44.428
<i>This is no</i>
<i>concern of yours.</i>

65
00:05:44.462 --> 00:05:46.297
My father wouldn't
send you.

66
00:05:49.835 --> 00:05:52.536
And I don't have to go
with you if I don't want.

67
00:05:52.570 --> 00:05:54.905
Take her.

68
00:05:54.939 --> 00:05:58.909
Are you men or snakes. that you
would threaten a child?

69
00:05:58.943 --> 00:06:01.078
Get out of my way.
little man.

70
00:06:01.112 --> 00:06:04.581
<i>I</i> am Syrio Forel...

71
00:06:04.615 --> 00:06:06.616
Foreign bastard.

72
00:06:09.353 --> 00:06:13.056
...And you will be speaking
to me with more respect.

73
00:06:13.090 --> 00:06:15.692
Kill the Braavosi.
Bring the girl.

74
00:06:17.229 --> 00:06:19.964
Arya child. we are done
with dancing for the day.

75
00:06:19.998 --> 00:06:22.633
Run to your father.

76
00:06:43.122 --> 00:06:45.857
Bloody oafs.

77
00:06:45.892 --> 00:06:47.759
Be gone now. Arya.

78
00:06:47.794 --> 00:06:50.363
Come with me.
Run.

79
00:06:51.999 --> 00:06:55.001
The First Sword of Braavos
does not run.

80
00:07:07.147 --> 00:07:09.048
What do we say

81
00:07:09.083 --> 00:07:11.017
to the God of Death?

82
00:07:11.051 --> 00:07:12.919
Not today.

83
00:07:14.454 --> 00:07:15.888
Go.

84
00:07:41.446 --> 00:07:43.548
Not today.
Not today.

85
00:07:53.092 --> 00:07:54.893
Stay away from me.

86
00:07:54.927 --> 00:07:56.594
I'll tell my father.

87
00:07:56.629 --> 00:07:59.597
I'll-- I'll tell
the Queen.

88
00:07:59.631 --> 00:08:03.334
Who do you think sent me?

89
00:08:15.847 --> 00:08:17.715
Needle.

90
00:08:20.953 --> 00:08:22.987
There she is.

91
00:08:23.022 --> 00:08:25.289
- What do you want?
- I want you. wolf girl.

92
00:08:25.324 --> 00:08:27.025
- Come here.
- Leave me be.

93
00:08:27.059 --> 00:08:29.126
My father's a lord.
He'll reward you.

94
00:08:29.161 --> 00:08:30.728
<i>She'll</i> reward me--
the Queen!

95
00:08:30.762 --> 00:08:32.930
Stay away!

96
00:09:02.028 --> 00:09:05.664
Lord Stark.
you must be thirsty.

97
00:09:07.100 --> 00:09:09.268
Varys.

98
00:09:11.071 --> 00:09:13.372
I promise you
it isn't poisoned.

99
00:09:15.042 --> 00:09:17.344
Why is it no one ever
trusts the eunuch?

100
00:09:25.887 --> 00:09:27.655
Not so much. My Lord.

101
00:09:27.690 --> 00:09:29.724
I would save the rest.
if I were you.

102
00:09:29.758 --> 00:09:33.628
Hide it. Men have been known to die
of thirst in these cells.

103
00:09:35.498 --> 00:09:38.000
What about
my daughters?

104
00:09:38.034 --> 00:09:40.569
The younger one seems
to have escaped the castle.

105
00:09:40.604 --> 00:09:42.805
Even my little birds
cannot find her.

106
00:09:42.839 --> 00:09:46.375
- And Sansa?
- Still engaged to Joffrey.

107
00:09:46.409 --> 00:09:49.979
Cersei will keep her close. The rest
of your household though--

108
00:09:50.013 --> 00:09:52.181
all dead.
it grieves me to say.

109
00:09:52.215 --> 00:09:54.483
I do so hate
the sight of blood.

110
00:09:55.985 --> 00:09:58.854
You watched my men being
slaughtered and did nothing.

111
00:09:58.888 --> 00:10:01.190
And would again. My Lord.

112
00:10:01.224 --> 00:10:05.627
I was unarmed. unarmored and
surrounded by Lannister swords.

113
00:10:05.662 --> 00:10:07.996
When you look at me
do you see a hero?

114
00:10:13.936 --> 00:10:16.304
What madness led you
to tell the Queen

115
00:10:16.339 --> 00:10:19.141
you had learned the truth
about Joffrey's birth?

116
00:10:21.511 --> 00:10:23.478
The madness of mercy.

117
00:10:25.181 --> 00:10:27.916
That she might
save her children.

118
00:10:27.951 --> 00:10:29.784
<i>Ah. the children.</i>

119
00:10:29.819 --> 00:10:32.688
It is always
the innocents who suffer.

120
00:10:32.722 --> 00:10:35.623
It wasn't the wine that killed Robert.
nor the boar.

121
00:10:35.658 --> 00:10:39.127
The wine slowed him down
and the boar ripped him open.

122
00:10:39.161 --> 00:10:42.396
but it was your mercy
that killed the King.

123
00:10:45.967 --> 00:10:49.336
I trust you know you are
a dead man. Lord Eddard?

124
00:10:54.074 --> 00:10:56.642
The Queen
can't kill me.

125
00:10:56.677 --> 00:10:59.145
Cat holds her brother.

126
00:10:59.180 --> 00:11:01.881
The wrong brother
sadly.

127
00:11:01.916 --> 00:11:03.650
And lost to her.

128
00:11:03.684 --> 00:11:06.619
Your wife has let the Imp
slip through her fingers.

129
00:11:10.458 --> 00:11:12.893
If that's true.

130
00:11:12.927 --> 00:11:16.463
then slit my throat
and be done with it.

131
00:11:16.497 --> 00:11:19.066
Not today. My Lord.

132
00:11:22.104 --> 00:11:24.939
Tell me something. Varys.

133
00:11:24.974 --> 00:11:27.476
Who do you truly serve?

134
00:11:28.712 --> 00:11:31.380
The Realm. My Lord.

135
00:11:31.415 --> 00:11:33.682
Someone must.

136
00:11:52.667 --> 00:11:55.403
It's Othor.
without a doubt.

137
00:11:56.739 --> 00:11:58.339
The other one is
Jafer Flowers. My Lord.

138
00:11:58.374 --> 00:12:01.142
<i>less the hand</i>
<i>the wolf tore off.</i>

139
00:12:01.177 --> 00:12:04.179
Any sign of Benjen
or the rest of his party?

140
00:12:04.214 --> 00:12:07.082
Just these two.
My Lord.

141
00:12:07.117 --> 00:12:09.118
Been dead awhile.
I'd say.

142
00:12:09.153 --> 00:12:11.888
- Mmm.
- The smell.

143
00:12:15.294 --> 00:12:16.894
What smell?

144
00:12:16.928 --> 00:12:19.964
There is none.

145
00:12:19.998 --> 00:12:23.734
If they'd be dead for a long time.
wouldn't there be rot?

146
00:12:23.768 --> 00:12:26.470
We should burn them.

147
00:12:26.504 --> 00:12:29.540
Snow's not wrong. My Lord.
Fire will do for them.

148
00:12:29.574 --> 00:12:31.742
The Wildling way.

149
00:12:31.777 --> 00:12:34.512
I want Maester Aemon
to examine them first.

150
00:12:34.546 --> 00:12:37.715
You may be
a coward. Tarly.

151
00:12:37.749 --> 00:12:39.884
<i>but you're not stupid.</i>

152
00:12:39.918 --> 00:12:43.954
- Get them inside.
- You heard him.

153
00:12:45.490 --> 00:12:47.458
Lord Commander.

154
00:12:47.492 --> 00:12:49.994
Maester Aemon awaits you
in his chambers--

155
00:12:50.028 --> 00:12:53.864
a raven
from King's Landing.

156
00:12:53.899 --> 00:12:55.766
Come on.
move 'em out.

157
00:13:07.477 --> 00:13:10.344
Bring me a horn
of ale. Snow.

158
00:13:10.379 --> 00:13:13.314
<i>and pour one</i>
<i>for yourself.</i>

159
00:13:23.125 --> 00:13:25.693
The King is dead.

160
00:13:37.805 --> 00:13:40.339
Is there any word
of my father?

161
00:13:40.373 --> 00:13:42.608
Sit.

162
00:13:47.113 --> 00:13:49.647
Lord Stark has been

163
00:13:49.681 --> 00:13:52.283
charged with treason.

164
00:13:52.317 --> 00:13:54.719
They say he conspired
with Robert's brothers

165
00:13:54.753 --> 00:13:57.489
to deny the throne
to Prince Joffrey.

166
00:14:09.838 --> 00:14:13.475
<i>I hope you're not thinking</i>
<i>of doing anything stupid.</i>

167
00:14:13.509 --> 00:14:16.945
Your duty lies here now.

168
00:14:16.979 --> 00:14:20.048
My sisters were
in King's Landing too.

169
00:14:22.185 --> 00:14:24.486
I'm sure they'll be

170
00:14:24.520 --> 00:14:26.321
treated gently.

171
00:14:29.458 --> 00:14:32.594
Your father has proved to be
an awful traitor. dear.

172
00:14:32.628 --> 00:14:36.098
King Robert's body
was still warm

173
00:14:36.132 --> 00:14:40.402
when Lord Eddard began plotting
to steal Joffrey's rightful throne.

174
00:14:40.437 --> 00:14:42.805
He wouldn't do that.

175
00:14:42.840 --> 00:14:45.708
He knows how much I love Joffrey.
He wouldn't.

176
00:14:45.743 --> 00:14:48.845
Please. Your Grace.
there's been a mistake.

177
00:14:48.879 --> 00:14:52.516
Send for my father. He'll tell you--
the King was his friend.

178
00:14:52.550 --> 00:14:55.619
Sansa sweetling. you are innocent of
any wrong. We know that.

179
00:14:55.653 --> 00:14:59.155
<i>Yet you are the daughter</i>
<i>of a traitor.</i>

180
00:14:59.189 --> 00:15:01.357
How can I allow you
to marry my son?

181
00:15:01.392 --> 00:15:04.560
<i>A child born</i>
<i>of a traitor's seed</i>

182
00:15:04.594 --> 00:15:06.928
is no fit consort
for our King.

183
00:15:06.963 --> 00:15:09.597
<i>She is a sweet thing now.</i>
<i>Your Grace.</i>

184
00:15:09.631 --> 00:15:12.099
but in 10 years who knows

185
00:15:12.133 --> 00:15:14.101
what treasons
she may hatch?

186
00:15:14.136 --> 00:15:17.204
No. I'm not. I'll be a good wife
to him. you'll see.

187
00:15:17.238 --> 00:15:21.809
I'll be a Queen just like you.
I promise. I won't hatch anything.

188
00:15:23.312 --> 00:15:25.813
The girl is innocent.
Your Grace.

189
00:15:25.848 --> 00:15:29.650
She should be given a chance
to prove her loyalty.

190
00:15:35.958 --> 00:15:38.860
Little dove. you must
write to Lady Catelyn

191
00:15:38.895 --> 00:15:41.229
and your brother.
the eldest. what's his name?

192
00:15:41.264 --> 00:15:42.998
Robb.

193
00:15:43.032 --> 00:15:45.801
Word of your father's arrest
will reach him soon. no doubt.

194
00:15:45.836 --> 00:15:48.237
Best it comes from you.

195
00:15:48.272 --> 00:15:50.640
If you would help
your father.

196
00:15:50.674 --> 00:15:53.110
urge your brother
to keep the King's peace.

197
00:15:53.144 --> 00:15:57.047
Tell him to come to King's Landing
and swear his fealty to Joffrey.

198
00:16:02.319 --> 00:16:06.689
If-- if I could see my father.
talk to him about--

199
00:16:09.292 --> 00:16:12.661
You disappoint me. child.

200
00:16:12.695 --> 00:16:14.996
We have told you
of your father's treason.

201
00:16:15.031 --> 00:16:17.198
Why would you want
to speak to a traitor?

202
00:16:17.233 --> 00:16:19.500
I only meant that--

203
00:16:21.704 --> 00:16:23.538
what will happen to him?

204
00:16:25.140 --> 00:16:28.942
- That depends.
- On-- on what?

205
00:16:28.976 --> 00:16:30.844
On your brother.

206
00:16:33.881 --> 00:16:36.216
And on you.

207
00:16:43.959 --> 00:16:46.728
Treason?

208
00:16:46.762 --> 00:16:48.897
Sansa wrote this?

209
00:16:48.931 --> 00:16:51.300
It is your sister's hand.
but the Queen's words.

210
00:16:51.334 --> 00:16:55.437
You are summoned to King's Landing
to swear fealty to the new King.

211
00:16:55.472 --> 00:16:58.574
Joffrey puts my father in chains.
now he wants his ass kissed?

212
00:16:58.608 --> 00:17:02.111
This is a royal
command. My Lord.

213
00:17:02.145 --> 00:17:05.614
- If you should refuse to obey--
- I won't refuse.

214
00:17:05.649 --> 00:17:08.417
His Grace summons me
to King's Landing.

215
00:17:08.451 --> 00:17:10.886
I'll go to King's Landing.

216
00:17:10.920 --> 00:17:13.655
But not alone.

217
00:17:15.758 --> 00:17:17.492
Call the banners.

218
00:17:19.194 --> 00:17:20.861
All of them. My Lord?

219
00:17:20.896 --> 00:17:22.767
They've all sworn to defend
my father. have they not?

220
00:17:22.792 --> 00:17:23.992
They have.

221
00:17:24.900 --> 00:17:27.168
Now we see what
their words are worth.

222
00:17:29.271 --> 00:17:30.438
Yeah.

223
00:17:38.681 --> 00:17:41.082
Are you afraid?

224
00:17:43.920 --> 00:17:45.620
I must be.

225
00:17:45.655 --> 00:17:47.823
Good.

226
00:17:47.857 --> 00:17:49.891
Why is that good?

227
00:17:49.926 --> 00:17:52.227
It means
you're not stupid.

228
00:18:15.618 --> 00:18:17.519
You've had this
since dawn?

229
00:18:18.554 --> 00:18:21.122
He sent it to me.
not you.

230
00:18:21.157 --> 00:18:23.591
I've only shown it
to you as a courtesy.

231
00:18:23.626 --> 00:18:25.493
A courtesy?!

232
00:18:25.527 --> 00:18:27.529
My husband has been
taken prisoner.

233
00:18:27.563 --> 00:18:29.197
My son intends
to declare war.

234
00:18:29.232 --> 00:18:31.099
A war?

235
00:18:31.133 --> 00:18:33.535
Your son against
the Lannisters?

236
00:18:34.870 --> 00:18:37.939
You should go to him.
Teach him patience.

237
00:18:37.973 --> 00:18:41.142
Ned rots in a dungeon
and you speak of patience?

238
00:18:41.177 --> 00:18:43.879
He is your brother by law!

239
00:18:43.913 --> 00:18:46.782
Does family mean
nothing to you?

240
00:18:46.816 --> 00:18:49.685
Family means
everything to me.

241
00:18:49.719 --> 00:18:52.154
And I will not
risk Robin's life

242
00:18:52.188 --> 00:18:54.657
to get caught up in another
of your husband's wars.

243
00:18:54.691 --> 00:18:57.593
- I'm hungry.
- Hush now. darling.

244
00:18:57.627 --> 00:18:59.828
You just ate.

245
00:18:59.863 --> 00:19:02.698
You will not support us then?
Do I understand you correctly?

246
00:19:02.732 --> 00:19:06.568
- But I'm hungry!
- Soon. love. soon.

247
00:19:08.605 --> 00:19:10.906
You're always
