497
00:43:05.595 --> 00:43:08.264
And now I find you
leading a host to war.

498
00:43:09.299 --> 00:43:11.701
- There was no one else.
- No one?

499
00:43:11.735 --> 00:43:14.470
Who were those men
I saw here?

500
00:43:14.505 --> 00:43:17.574
- None of them are Starks.
- All of them are seasoned in battle.

501
00:43:17.608 --> 00:43:20.644
If you think you can send me back
to Winterfell--

502
00:43:20.678 --> 00:43:22.946
Oh. would that I could.

503
00:43:26.017 --> 00:43:27.985
There was...

504
00:43:28.019 --> 00:43:30.454
a letter.

505
00:43:32.891 --> 00:43:34.326
From Sansa.

506
00:43:35.294 --> 00:43:37.595
From the Queen.
you mean.

507
00:43:45.569 --> 00:43:48.671
- There's no mention of Arya.
- No.

508
00:43:59.282 --> 00:44:01.616
How many men
do you have?

509
00:44:01.650 --> 00:44:04.052
18.000.

510
00:44:04.086 --> 00:44:06.554
If I go to King's Landing
and bend my knee to Joffrey--

511
00:44:06.588 --> 00:44:09.657
you would never
be allowed to leave. No.

512
00:44:09.691 --> 00:44:12.460
Our best hope--
our only hope--

513
00:44:12.494 --> 00:44:15.797
is that you can defeat
them in the field.

514
00:44:15.831 --> 00:44:17.865
And if I lose?

515
00:44:17.899 --> 00:44:20.434
Do you know what happened
to the Targaryen children

516
00:44:20.469 --> 00:44:23.472
- when the Mad King fell?
- They were butchered in their sleep.

517
00:44:23.506 --> 00:44:26.208
On the orders
of Tywin Lannister.

518
00:44:26.242 --> 00:44:28.945
And the years have
not made him kinder.

519
00:44:32.049 --> 00:44:34.218
If you lose.

520
00:44:34.252 --> 00:44:36.954
your father dies.

521
00:44:36.988 --> 00:44:38.522
your sisters die.

522
00:44:38.556 --> 00:44:40.790
<i>we</i> die.

523
00:44:43.360 --> 00:44:45.394
Well. that makes it
simple then.

524
00:44:46.730 --> 00:44:48.730
I suppose it does.

525
00:45:11.752 --> 00:45:14.987
From here it might be best if
Bronn and I continue alone.

526
00:45:15.022 --> 00:45:17.591
Best for Tyrion
son of Tywin.

527
00:45:17.625 --> 00:45:19.626
Not best for me.

528
00:45:19.660 --> 00:45:22.830
If the half man betrays us.

529
00:45:22.864 --> 00:45:26.300
Shagga Son of Dolf
will cut off his manhood--

530
00:45:26.335 --> 00:45:28.870
and feed it
to the goats. yes.

531
00:45:31.374 --> 00:45:33.942
All right then.

532
00:45:33.976 --> 00:45:36.178
Time to meet my father.

533
00:46:08.511 --> 00:46:11.313
- Tyrion.
- Uncle.

534
00:46:11.347 --> 00:46:13.215
Father.

535
00:46:14.718 --> 00:46:17.719
The rumors of your demise
were unfounded.

536
00:46:17.754 --> 00:46:21.155
Sorry
to disappoint you.

537
00:46:21.190 --> 00:46:23.725
And who are these...

538
00:46:23.759 --> 00:46:25.993
<i>Companions</i> of yours?

539
00:46:28.063 --> 00:46:30.496
This is Shagga
Son of Dolf.

540
00:46:30.531 --> 00:46:32.899
<i>Chieftain</i>
<i>of the Stone Crows.</i>

541
00:46:32.933 --> 00:46:37.303
<i>Timett Son of Timett.</i>
<i>ruler of the Burned Men.</i>

542
00:46:37.337 --> 00:46:42.075
<i>This fair maid is</i>
<i>Chella daughter of Cheyk.</i>

543
00:46:42.109 --> 00:46:44.478
<i>leader</i>
<i>of the Black Ears.</i>

544
00:46:44.512 --> 00:46:47.881
And here we have
Bronn son of...

545
00:46:47.916 --> 00:46:50.518
You wouldn't know him.

546
00:46:52.521 --> 00:46:55.090
May I present
My Lord Father.

547
00:46:55.124 --> 00:46:57.759
Tywin son of Tytos
of House Lannister.

548
00:46:57.794 --> 00:47:00.862
<i>Lord of Casterly Rock</i>
<i>and Warden of the West?</i>

549
00:47:02.832 --> 00:47:05.468
Kind of you
to go to war for me.

550
00:47:08.505 --> 00:47:10.439
You left us no choice.

551
00:47:10.474 --> 00:47:12.541
The honor of the House
was at stake.

552
00:47:14.044 --> 00:47:17.213
Your brother would never have
submitted to capture so meekly.

553
00:47:17.248 --> 00:47:19.782
We have our differences.
Jaime and I.

554
00:47:19.817 --> 00:47:21.985
He's braver.
I'm better looking.

555
00:47:22.019 --> 00:47:24.354
He's been covering himself
in glory.

556
00:47:24.389 --> 00:47:27.625
Jaime smashed the River Lords
at the Golden Tooth.

557
00:47:27.659 --> 00:47:31.328
and now lays siege to Riverrun.
Catelyn Stark's homeland.

558
00:47:31.362 --> 00:47:33.463
And the Starks?
Lord Eddard?

559
00:47:33.497 --> 00:47:37.567
--Is our hostage. He will lead
no armies from his dungeon cell.

560
00:47:37.602 --> 00:47:39.636
How did my sweet sister
persuade the King

561
00:47:39.670 --> 00:47:41.538
to imprison
his dear friend Ned?

562
00:47:41.573 --> 00:47:45.543
Robert Baratheon is dead.
Joffrey rules in King's Landing.

563
00:47:48.548 --> 00:47:50.516
My sister rules.
you mean.

564
00:47:51.718 --> 00:47:54.019
Stark's son has
called his banners.

565
00:47:54.054 --> 00:47:57.490
- He moves south with a strong host.
- A green boy.

566
00:47:57.524 --> 00:47:59.291
One taste of battle
and he'll run

567
00:47:59.326 --> 00:48:01.895
back to Winterfell
with his tail between his legs.

568
00:48:03.097 --> 00:48:04.597
Maybe.

569
00:48:04.631 --> 00:48:07.200
Though the boy does have
a certain belligerence.

570
00:48:07.234 --> 00:48:09.736
You'd like him.

571
00:48:09.770 --> 00:48:13.807
While we're on
the subject of war.

572
00:48:13.841 --> 00:48:16.543
I made promises
to my friends here

573
00:48:16.577 --> 00:48:18.945
and a Lannister
always pays his debts.

574
00:48:18.979 --> 00:48:22.048
<i>We shall require</i>
<i>3.000 helms and shields.</i>

575
00:48:22.083 --> 00:48:24.317
plus swords. pikes.

576
00:48:24.351 --> 00:48:26.152
gorgets. maces--

577
00:48:26.186 --> 00:48:28.754
if it please My Lord.

578
00:48:28.788 --> 00:48:30.856
Ser Addam bids me report
that the Northmen

579
00:48:30.890 --> 00:48:32.290
have crossed the Neck.

580
00:48:34.293 --> 00:48:36.761
The wolf rushes
into the lion's jaws.

581
00:48:36.795 --> 00:48:41.032
So be it. Kevan. command the
drummers beat assembly.

582
00:48:42.535 --> 00:48:45.671
And send word to Jaime that
I am moving against Robb Stark.

583
00:48:45.705 --> 00:48:47.673
At once. My Lord.

584
00:49:00.622 --> 00:49:03.590
It is said that the men of the
Mountain clans are great warriors.

585
00:49:03.625 --> 00:49:05.359
Ride with me
against my enemies

586
00:49:05.393 --> 00:49:08.429
and you shall have all
my son promised you and more.

587
00:49:08.464 --> 00:49:10.698
Only if the half man
fights with us.

588
00:49:10.733 --> 00:49:14.169
Until we hold the steel
he pledged us.

589
00:49:14.204 --> 00:49:16.605
the little lion's
life is ours.

590
00:49:22.178 --> 00:49:24.847
<i>The scouts report</i>
<i>Lord Tywin moves north.</i>

591
00:49:24.881 --> 00:49:26.715
We need to get him
on broken ground.

592
00:49:26.750 --> 00:49:28.417
put his Knights
at a disadvantage.

593
00:49:28.451 --> 00:49:30.553
No. we need to get
around him

594
00:49:30.587 --> 00:49:33.489
and break Jaime Lannister's
siege of Riverrun.

595
00:49:33.524 --> 00:49:36.359
Do that and the River Lords
will join us.

596
00:49:36.393 --> 00:49:38.261
To do either we need to cross
the river

597
00:49:38.295 --> 00:49:39.962
and the only crossing
is at The Twins.

598
00:49:39.996 --> 00:49:42.031
<i>Lord Frey controls</i>
<i>that bridge.</i>

599
00:49:42.065 --> 00:49:43.632
Your father's bannerman.

600
00:49:43.666 --> 00:49:46.902
"The late Lord Frey"
my father calls him.

601
00:49:46.936 --> 00:49:50.439
At the Trident. he didn't appear
until the battle was done.

602
00:49:50.473 --> 00:49:54.510
Some men takes their oaths
more seriously than others.

603
00:50:01.918 --> 00:50:04.653
Robb's right.
We need that bridge.

604
00:50:04.687 --> 00:50:06.788
So what's it going to be?

605
00:50:06.823 --> 00:50:10.225
Do we move against
Jaime or Lord Tywin?

606
00:50:14.397 --> 00:50:15.931
Your pardon. my lords.

607
00:50:15.965 --> 00:50:18.634
<i>We've captured</i>
<i>a Lannister scout.</i>

608
00:50:20.537 --> 00:50:23.873
Don't worry. lad. He won't be
leaving this tent with his head.

609
00:50:25.209 --> 00:50:26.876
Where did you find him?

610
00:50:26.911 --> 00:50:29.045
In the brush above
the encampment.

611
00:50:29.079 --> 00:50:30.947
<i>He looked to be counting.</i>

612
00:50:41.392 --> 00:50:43.193
How high did you get?

613
00:50:45.563 --> 00:50:47.564
20.000.
Maybe more.

614
00:50:48.599 --> 00:50:50.333
You don't have
to do this yourself.

615
00:50:50.367 --> 00:50:51.934
Your father
would understand--

616
00:50:51.969 --> 00:50:56.005
My father understands mercy.
when there is room for it.

617
00:50:57.407 --> 00:50:59.241
And he understands honor...

618
00:51:02.046 --> 00:51:04.313
and courage.

619
00:51:06.216 --> 00:51:08.050
Let him go.

620
00:51:09.019 --> 00:51:11.420
Robb.

621
00:51:23.432 --> 00:51:26.400
Tell Lord Tywin
Winter is coming for him.

622
00:51:26.434 --> 00:51:31.371
20.000 Northerners marching south
to find out if he really does shit gold.

623
00:51:33.441 --> 00:51:34.941
Yes. My Lord.

624
00:51:34.975 --> 00:51:36.777
Thank you. My Lord.

625
00:51:46.221 --> 00:51:49.923
Are you touched. boy?!
Letting him go?

626
00:51:49.958 --> 00:51:51.993
You call me boy again.

627
00:51:53.495 --> 00:51:55.129
Go on.

628
00:52:12.145 --> 00:52:15.347
Oi.

629
00:52:20.419 --> 00:52:23.088
<i>It is also the wish</i>
<i>of His Grace</i>

630
00:52:23.123 --> 00:52:28.428
<i>that his loyal servant</i>
<i>Janos Slynt.</i>

631
00:52:28.462 --> 00:52:31.565
- <i>Commander of the City Watch...</i>
- Ser Aron.

632
00:52:31.599 --> 00:52:35.169
<i>...Be at once raised</i>
<i>to the rank of Lord...</i>

633
00:52:35.203 --> 00:52:40.674
- Lord Gyles.
- <i>...And granted the ancient seat of Harrenhal.</i>

634
00:52:40.708 --> 00:52:44.544
<i>and that his sons and grandsons</i>
<i>shall hold this honor</i>

635
00:52:44.578 --> 00:52:49.682
<i>after him</i>
<i>until the end of time.</i>

636
00:52:53.519 --> 00:52:56.854
In the place of the traitor
Eddard Stark.

637
00:52:56.889 --> 00:53:01.559
<i>it is the wish of His Grace</i>
<i>that Tywin Lannister.</i>

638
00:53:01.593 --> 00:53:05.396
<i>Lord of Casterly Rock</i>
<i>and Warden of the West.</i>

639
00:53:05.431 --> 00:53:09.534
<i>be appointed</i>
<i>Hand of the King.</i>

640
00:53:09.568 --> 00:53:11.469
Lastly.

641
00:53:11.504 --> 00:53:14.338
in these times
of treason and turmoil.

642
00:53:14.372 --> 00:53:17.608
<i>it is the view</i>
<i>of the Council</i>

643
00:53:17.643 --> 00:53:20.177
that the life and safety

644
00:53:20.212 --> 00:53:22.880
of King Joffrey

645
00:53:22.914 --> 00:53:27.151
be of paramount importance.

646
00:53:28.754 --> 00:53:31.288
Ser Barristan Selmy.

647
00:53:37.629 --> 00:53:41.132
Your Grace. I am
yours to command.

648
00:53:41.166 --> 00:53:43.268
Rise. Ser Barristan.

649
00:53:44.137 --> 00:53:46.238
You may remove
your helm.

650
00:53:51.179 --> 00:53:53.781
<i>You have served the Realm</i>
<i>long and faithfully.</i>

651
00:53:53.815 --> 00:53:57.785
<i>Every man and woman in the</i>
<i>Seven Kingdoms owes you thanks.</i>

652
00:53:57.820 --> 00:54:01.088
But it is time to put aside
your armor and your sword.

653
00:54:01.122 --> 00:54:04.025
<i>It is time to rest</i>
<i>and look back with pride</i>

654
00:54:04.059 --> 00:54:05.693
on your many years
of service.

655
00:54:07.897 --> 00:54:10.331
Your Grace. the Kingsguard
is a sworn brotherhood.

656
00:54:10.366 --> 00:54:12.533
<i>Our vows are</i>
<i>taken for life.</i>

657
00:54:12.568 --> 00:54:15.070
Only death relieves us
of our sacred trust.

658
00:54:15.104 --> 00:54:18.807
Whose death. Ser Barristan?
Yours or your King's?

659
00:54:18.841 --> 00:54:21.710
<i>You let my father die.</i>

660
00:54:21.744 --> 00:54:24.680
You're too old
to protect anybody.

661
00:54:26.984 --> 00:54:29.719
- Your Grace--
- The Council has determined

662
00:54:29.753 --> 00:54:32.188
that Ser Jaime Lannister
will take your place

663
00:54:32.223 --> 00:54:34.491
<i>as Lord Commander</i>
<i>of the Kingsguard.</i>

664
00:54:34.525 --> 00:54:36.059
The man who
profaned his blade

665
00:54:36.094 --> 00:54:38.295
with the blood of the King
he had sworn to defend!

666
00:54:38.329 --> 00:54:40.263
Careful. Ser.

667
00:54:40.297 --> 00:54:41.998
We have nothing
but gratitude

668
00:54:42.032 --> 00:54:44.501
for your long service.
good Ser.

669
00:54:44.535 --> 00:54:47.003
You shall be given
a stout Keep beside the sea.

670
00:54:47.037 --> 00:54:49.372
with servants
to look after your every need.

671
00:54:49.406 --> 00:54:51.607
A hall to die in

672
00:54:51.642 --> 00:54:54.043
<i>and men to bury me.</i>

673
00:54:55.645 --> 00:54:58.681
I am a Knight.

674
00:54:58.715 --> 00:55:01.751
I shall die a Knight.

675
00:55:07.691 --> 00:55:09.826
A naked Knight.
apparently.

676
00:55:20.971 --> 00:55:24.407
Even now I could cut through
the five of you like carving a cake!

677
00:55:28.579 --> 00:55:31.113
Here. boy!

678
00:55:31.148 --> 00:55:33.583
Melt it down and add it
to the others.

679
00:55:50.099 --> 00:55:52.434
If any man in this hall
has other matters

680
00:55:52.468 --> 00:55:55.603
to set before His Grace.
let him speak now

681
00:55:55.638 --> 00:55:58.874
or go forth and hold
his silence.

682
00:56:01.545 --> 00:56:03.680
Your Grace.

683
00:56:03.714 --> 00:56:06.083
Come forward.
My Lady.

684
00:56:07.852 --> 00:56:10.588
<i>The Lady Sansa</i>
<i>of House Stark.</i>

685
00:56:12.124 --> 00:56:15.526
Do you have some business for
the King and the Council. Sansa?

686
00:56:15.561 --> 00:56:17.395
I do.

687
00:56:22.267 --> 00:56:25.369
As it please Your Grace.
I ask mercy for my father.

688
00:56:25.403 --> 00:56:28.873
Lord Eddard Stark.
who was Hand of the King.

689
00:56:28.907 --> 00:56:31.775
Treason is a noxious weed.

690
00:56:31.810 --> 00:56:35.980
- It should be torn out. root--
- Let her speak.

691
00:56:36.015 --> 00:56:38.717
I want to hear
what she says.

692
00:56:38.751 --> 00:56:40.886
Thank you. Your Grace.

693
00:56:40.920 --> 00:56:43.523
Do you deny
your father's crime?

694
00:56:43.557 --> 00:56:48.028
No. My Lords.
I know he must be punished.

695
00:56:48.062 --> 00:56:50.063
All I ask is mercy.

696
00:56:50.098 --> 00:56:52.967
<i>I know My Lord father</i>
<i>must regret what he did.</i>

697
00:56:53.001 --> 00:56:55.303
He was King Robert's friend
and he loved him.

698
00:56:55.337 --> 00:56:57.538
You all know he loved him.

699
00:56:57.573 --> 00:57:01.175
He never wanted to be Hand
until the King asked him.

700
00:57:01.209 --> 00:57:04.611
They must have lied to him--
Lord Renly or Lord Stannis

701
00:57:04.645 --> 00:57:07.447
or somebody.
They must have lied!

702
00:57:07.482 --> 00:57:09.950
He said
I wasn't the King.

703
00:57:09.984 --> 00:57:12.051
Why did he say that?

704
00:57:12.086 --> 00:57:14.354
He was badly hurt.

705
00:57:14.388 --> 00:57:17.256
Maester Pycelle was giving
him milk of the poppy.

706
00:57:17.290 --> 00:57:21.460
He wasn't himself. Otherwise h
never would have said it.

707
00:57:23.796 --> 00:57:27.666
A child's faith...
Such sweet innocence.

708
00:57:27.700 --> 00:57:31.370
<i>And yet they say</i>
<i>wisdom oft comes</i>

709
00:57:31.405 --> 00:57:33.239
from the mouths of babes.

710
00:57:33.273 --> 00:57:37.410
Treason
is treason!

711
00:57:40.548 --> 00:57:42.715
Anything else?

712
00:57:44.285 --> 00:57:47.687
If you still have any affection
in your heart for me.

713
00:57:47.721 --> 00:57:51.223
please do me
this kindness. Your Grace.

714
00:58:00.800 --> 00:58:03.067
Your sweet words
have moved me.

715
00:58:05.471 --> 00:58:08.038
But your father has
to confess.

716
00:58:08.073 --> 00:58:11.675
He has to confess
and say that I'm the King...

717
00:58:14.578 --> 00:58:16.713
Or there'll be
no mercy for him.

718
00:58:21.185 --> 00:58:23.286
He will.

719
00:58:33.322 --> 00:58:37.322
== sync. corrected by <font color="#00ff00">elderman</font> ==

719
00:58:38.305 --> 00:59:38.861
